ups; • Explores emerging areas of growing political interest such as radicalisation; • Employs case studies and examples from practice to aid student understanding. Including helpful key points to guide reading at the beginning of each chapter, as well as exercises for seminars and further reading recommendations, this text will be an invaluable resource to all students in social work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aBrown, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCummins, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCummins, Ian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMassie, Scott, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMort, Lucy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoth, Rich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParkinson, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParkinson, Kate, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPeach, Donna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPollock, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPollock, Sarah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWilliams, Ben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWithers, Alex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYianni, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z97831111966880 cprintz978144734470440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447344735423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/978